; Renders a fixed-width text field to the CheckIt screen. Five far-call args
; (caller cleans 10 bytes via 'add sp, 0x000a'): [bp+06]:[bp+08]=source string
; far ptr, [bp+0a]=max field width (char count), [bp+0c]:[bp+0e]=far ptr to
; field descriptor struct. Iterates source string up to max_width chars: NUL
; terminates early (sets end-of-string flag [bp-0x18]=1), TAB (0x09) and LF
